  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Egypt: Strengthening and Expanding HIV-Related Legal Services and Rights - Phase III</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. To improve access to high-quality HIV-related legal and health care services. 2. To strengthen the legal and policy environment for HIV prevention and treatment.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aimed at building the capacity of legal and public health actors in Egypt to further develop an enabling legal and public health environment for the national response to HIV, focusing on legal services for people living with HIV and key affected populations, as well as access to medicines for the treatment of HIV.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project direct and indirect beneficiaries included: Non-governmental legal sector actors, public health advocates; people living with HIV; key populations, such as sex workers, drug users, and men who have sex with men; and Government legal sector and public health officials</narrative>
  </description>
